ANTHRAX, HUMAN - KAZAKHSTAN (02): (EAST KAZAKHSTAN), CONFIRMED
**************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 27 Sep 2011
Source: Gazeta.KZ, KazTAG (Kazakh Telegraph Agency) report [in
Russian, trans., edited]
http://news.gazeta.kz/art.asp?aid=349204


Quarantine measures have been set up in the village of Makanchi in
[Urdzharsky] district of East Kazakhstan where 19 people were exposed
to possible anthrax and are under health watch. This was reported by
the press service of the Department of Emergency SAI, reports KazTAG.
At this time 18 of them are local folk from Makanchi, and one in
Semey. All are being tested every day and are under the supervision of
physicians.

Strict movement controls of livestock and meat are in place. The
source of infection has not yet been identified. In the meanwhile the
house and yard of the affected patient have been cleaned and
disinfected.

As previously reported, on 22 Sep 2011 a 45-year-old man from Makanchi
was hospitalised in the district hospital with suspected anthrax. As
of 26 Sep 2011 the diagnosis has been laboratory confirmed.

In eastern Kazakhstan, there are about 200 historic anthrax foci.
Recent cases were reported in 2008 in Ulan Ayagoz in the Eastern
region.

